      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAINT BREE (1) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at her last five runs. Last time finished 2nd on June 28 over 305m at this track behind Energy To Burn beaten 4.5 lengths (17.87) in a Grade 5. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Likely to be in the finish again. SHANNY ROSE (3) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 17.76 beating Costly Habits. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. Looks a key chance if runs up to latest figure. MY MATE ROBBIE (2) has a terrific record this track and trip with two wins and one placing from three starts. In the money last time at this track (23.32) in a Grade 5, finishing a 6 length third. Makes strong appeal on best. COMPTON LIZZIE (8) drops in journey and should be in the mix.",
